programmes.show_description: This Is CBeebies. Programmes start at 6.00am.
Baby Jake Loves Spinning in Space. Baby Jake and the Hamsternauts go on a space adventure and play spinning.
Bullet Train, Japan. Meet the Go Jetters, four explorers on a global adventure! All aboard for a high-speed adventure, as the Go Jetters visit Japan's bullet train.
Mine. Children's animation. Bing and Pando are tired but insist on one last game of hide-and-seek. Pando hides in Bing's bed, but by the time Bing finds him he is fast asleep.
Sparkle and Shine Day. Love Monster trades in his old scooter for a shiny new one but finds he can no longer do a lot of the fun things on it that he used to do with his old one.
It Came from Planet Boogie. A crashed meteor in the town square makes every machine in Swoppiton dance... even Mojo!
Wild Safari Park. Mtambo enlists Wilson's help to feed the animals at Safari Park. Now if only Wilson could remember what food to feed which animal!
Play Rock. The baby Pea-Rexes fight over a rock, so Ginger arranges a timeshare to let them all play.
Lychee. Live from the Roots and Fruits theatre, it's love and peace symbol Lychee performing his song All You Need Is Lychee!   Followed by My Petsaurus.
Tablet Takeover. The Veggies are delighted with a new tablet they've found. When they're not looking, Evil Pea turns the tablet to evil mode. Soon the tablet takes over the supermarket.
Skateboard. Children's animation. Bing can't wait to have a go on a skateboard, but it's much harder to balance than Pando made it look.
Nicky. Bing shows Sula's cousin how to voosh a toy car down a slide - but then things go wrong.
The Board Game Badge. It is a rainy day in the clubhouse, which means it's a perfect day for a board game.
The Direction Badge. The Squirrels go out for a walk but can't find a way back to the clubhouse.
The Paddy Fields of China. Animated adventure comedy series. The Go Jetters swing into action when Glitch uses real landmarks for his crazy golf course.
The Tale of the Downhill Escape. Animated series. Peter takes Benjamin and Lily on a wild ride down a steep slope. When Benjamin gets injured, Peter has to navigate them to safety.
The Dolphin Reef Rescue. Animated deep sea adventures with Captain Barnacles and his explorers. The Octonauts all pitch in to help save a sick coral reef.
Runaway Tour. Preston's automated scooter tour of Swoppiton doesn't go as planned. Mojo and Bo must find a way to chase down and scoop up those scooters, and get the tour back on track!
Pot Shot. When a rogue ball destroys Mr Parks's competition-ready bug hotel, Evie, Taran and Jaz help him rebuild it using a combination of football skills and teamwork.
The Wheels Go Round. Ben meets his new friends at the farm to look for big and small wheels. Meanwhile, Mr Tumble plays bus driver with the toys.
The Sleepover. A sleepover with their cousin means Bluey and Bingo get to stay up late!
Housework. Mum and Dad vow to only finish their boring housework when the kids stop acting silly!
The Sharing Badge. Duggee and the Squirrels bake a pie and learn how to share by dividing things equally.
The History Badge. The Squirrels get a special history lesson from Duggee and some faces from the past.
...of the Unexpected Discovery. Peter Rabbit Special: The Tale of the Unexpected Discovery. After Peter saves a friend, he is rewarded with something very special.
The Valley of Balls, Kazakhstan. Meet the Go Jetters, four explorers on a global adventure! Can the Go Jetters take control of a rocky situation in the Valley of Balls?
Mission Masterpiece. The Weasy family perform a heist to retrieve a painting from the farmer.
Adventures in Fossil Hunting/Lizard's Buggy Bonanza. Von Carnegie goes missing. Lizard supersizes bugs.
Mountain Parrots. When birds cause trouble aboard the Octoray, Tweak uses her Octowatch to help with repairs.
Den. Seamus and Little Woo are spotting wildlife in the woods, so Stanley builds them a special camouflaged den to watch quietly without scaring the creatures.
The Dough Blob. Evil Pea makes a giant dough blob so that she can take over the supermarket. The Tato Team must use some baking know-how to save the day.

programmes.show_name: New: Talking Tom Heroes: Suddenly Super
programmes.show_description: Quark's Day Out. Hank becomes friends with Professor Kranium's robot sidekick.
Diplodocus and Dung. Children's dinosaur history series. Andy travels back 152 million years, to the time of diplodocus - a massive 25-metre-long plant-eating dinosaur.
Busy the Bee. Jen is a rock star in the cafe today, but Small is too small to play the instruments.
Acorns. Ranger Hamza and the Ramblers go on an eco quest to find out all about acorns.
Vulture and Brittlestar. Aneeshwar and Lizzie meet two amazing animals and reveal a surprising connection between them in the wild. This time, it's vultures and brittlestars.
Waffle and the Marching Band. Waffle's smelliness threatens his role in a marching band sing along for Mr Nolan.
The Show and Tell Badge. Animated preschool series. Duggee has something really interesting to show at the clubhouse. Can the Squirrels find some other interesting things to share?
Jawfish. Animated deep sea adventures with Captain Barnacles and his explorers. A mouthbrooding jawfish father has lost his eggs, and the Octonauts must help get them back to him!
Juno's Wiggly Tooth. When Juno the hippo has her first loose tooth, Vida helps her prepare for the tooth fairy.
The Great Wall of China. Animated adventure comedy series. Glitch and his grimbots have a long race on a very long wall - the Great Wall of China!
The Gingerbread Wish. Rafi's gingerbread wish brings her bakes to life. She discovers perfect can mean different things, and messy can be special too.
All Change. Yukee is struggling with a tune on her ukulele, so she tells her friends she's going to give it up.
Parsley. Live from the Roots and Fruits theatre, it's Parsley performing Rise Up with Me.
Farmyard Fun. Meet some cute alpacas with Justin and his friend as they visit a farm, while Mr Tumble, Grandad Tumble and Aunt Polly sing Old MacDonald at the farmyard dance.
Trees. Gemma, Bailee Bear and Benjee Bear invite little ones and their grown-ups to explore trees through play, song and storytelling. Toddlers and grown-ups at home can join in too.
What's It Like to Be a Tree? Kiri and Lou try out being trees, which is mostly about keeping still, and make a very large new friend named Moa.
Potluck Picnic. Wilf thinks he's been left out of a picnic, so he sulks and builds a huge tower. The Piggies must convince him to join them before the tower collapses.
Mission: Missing Map. Meagaidh the search and rescue dog must find Annie, who is lost with her kayak, fast!
Tickle. Preschool animation about a baby monkey and his mother. Mo can make Tee crack-up laughing with one tickle, but Tee is unable to get her to laugh in return.
A Few Dinos Too Many! The Game Catchers find themselves on a Beachy Planet and learn to play the game pour and fill. They need to be creative when making more materials for the game!
Cafe. Elsee joins her friend Fiadh at a local caf√© for a game of I-spy.
School Crossing Patroller. Dylan wants to help kids get to school safely using his stop sign.
The Sticky Sauce Situation. Fabio's sticky sauce gets him stuck to Mojo. Is there really no way to unstick them?
Tom's Flying Fist Bump. Tom goes overboard using the Flying Fist Bump without understanding how to control it.
Water Butts. Ranger Hamza and the Ramblers learn why water butts are good for the environment. They make their own mini water butts by recycling old items.
Operation Seal. The Piris believe a seal colony is planning a takeover, but are their fears justified?
Go Jet Academy: Ghost Crabs. Glitch damages the Academy crabs' habitat when he takes all the sand from their beach.
Food Glorious Food. Dixie and friends dream of the delicious food they could have when faced with gruel.
Pippen's Stomach Bug. When her brother has a stomach bug, Pippen is afraid she will catch it!
One Whole Year. It's been one year since Cosima crash landed on Proxima, but no-one else has remembered this anniversary! Can a perfect picnic jolt their memories?
Burger Shop. It's time for Bluey and Bingo to get out of the bath, but Dad gets roped into a game.
Nikhil and Jay and the Swapsies Day. Appa is doing Amma jobs, and Amma is doing Appa jobs - it's swapsies day! After swapping toys, Nikhil and Jay decide to swap being each other.
It's Time for a Tea Party. JoJo and Gran Gran go to a Tyrannosaurus tea party at the museum!
Fairground. Animation. Sarah and her best friend Duck embark on simple but exciting adventures. A fair is being held in the park, which means Sarah and Duck can't find their bench.
Boo! Made You Jump! Children's animation with the siblings. It is easy for Charlie to make Lola jump. Lola wants to make Charlie jump, and tries hiding, ghosts and scary stories.
Pepi Nana and Mr Onion in the Tub! Pepi Nana finds the little toy tub hiding in her wardrobe. Little Nana wishes the little toy tub was a great big tub.
Rainbows. MeMo and BaBa notice a rainbow in the sky after the rain stops, but where does it end? They embark on a journey to find more rainbows all over Planet BeddyByes.
Makka Pakka Washes Faces. Series for young children. Makka Pakka visits the inhabitants of the garden to wash their faces. Everyone loves it - even the teeny tiny Pontipines.
JJ Chalmers - What Happened to You. JJ Chalmers reads a story about accepting difference.
This Is CBeebies. Programmes start at 6.00am.
Baby Jake Loves Bumpety Bump. The adventures of magical Baby Jake and friends. Baby Jake and Nibbles the Rabbit go on a countryside adventure and play bumpety bump.
Go Jet Academy: Wind Power. Meet the Go Jetters, four explorers on a global adventure! The Go Jetters race to save Glitch when his kite flies too close to the academy's windfarm.
Lunch. Children's animation. Bing and Sula help Amma to get lunch ready. Bing watches yummy peas and delicious carrots go into the pot.
Breakfast for Dinner Day. Love Monster has planned the perfect dinner for his friends, but things start to go wrong.
Breakdown Bryan. Bryan the ferry can't shut his engine off, so he's speeding out of control around the lake. How will Mojo and Bo get aboard to take control and steer Bryan to safety?
Frostini's True Calling. When a fancy new ice cream machine comes to Chuggington, Frostini feels left behind and goes in search of his true passion.
The Following Forest. Ginger and the Pea-Rexes help an Asparagusaur, and it starts following them everywhere.
Broccoli. Live from the Roots and Fruits theatre, it's Broccoli and his floret Broc performing their phenomenal ventriloquist act.   Followed by My Petsaurus.
Carrot's Big Top. Carrot is starring in a circus, but problems arise when Evil Pea meddles with her tricks.
Butterfly. Children's animation. When a butterfly lands on Sula's painting, Bing tries to help it go back outside, but he holds it too tightly and the poor butterfly is squished.
Face Paint. Sula paints Bing to look like Biteysaurus, but upsets Bing by accidentally adding purple.
The Perfume Badge. The Squirrels make their very own perfumes with accompanying advertisements to show how their perfumes are uniquely theirs.
The Building Block Badge. The Squirrels become architects so they can design, build and bring to life their very own clubhouse.
Cappadocia, Turkey. Animated adventure comedy series. A game of hide-and-seek threatens to topple the fairy chimneys of Cappadocia in Turkey.
The Tale of the Cat and the Rat. Animated series. When Jemima and the ducklings are driven from their coop, Peter must enlist the unwitting help of Mr McGregor's cat.
The Eel Ordeal. Animated deep sea adventures with Captain Barnacles and his explorers. The Octonauts travel up a treacherous river to help a young migrating eel.
Watch the Birdie. Preston's stuck in a balloon, and only Mojo and Bo can get him back on the ground.
Loop, Swoop and Pull. Elvis must learn to tie his own laces quickly to achieve his PB in goalkeeping.
At the Doctors. Maddie joins her friend for a check up at the doctor's. Meanwhile, Mr Tumble is playing doctor with the toys.
Early Baby. Bluey's playgroup is at odds when Indy's baby hospital collides with Rusty's knights.
Pass the Parcel. Lucky's dad changes the rules of pass the parcel back to having one prize in the middle.
The Art Badge. The Squirrels learn about different types of art and what inspires them while preparing their own pieces for Tino the Artistic Mouse's Woodland Biennale.
The Crazy Golf Badge. Duggee and the Squirrels practise their golf in pursuit of a round of milkshakes.
When You Wish Upon a Whale. Norman misses his whale friends. The Piris try to help, but his size proves a challenge.
Personal Space. When Cosima finally finds a quiet place to read her book, she realises peace and quiet aren't all they're made out to be. Where's Big Lizard when she needs him?
Roar Off. Ginger and the baby Pea-Rexes start a massive roar off with all the other Vegesaurs.
Gliding, Argentina. Meet the Go Jetters, four explorers on a global adventure! Glitch gatecrashes an academy gliding test, causing calamity in the skies over Argentina.
Mission Showtime. Spicy directs a show without Weasy, so he forces his way onto the stage.
Too Many Zolas/Electro's Glow Show. Zola duplicates himself. Electro makes electric bugs.
Mystery Island. When Kwazii and Calico Jack get stranded on an island, the Octonauts must search for them.
Flower. Fifi's sunbell flower needs protection to grow, so Stan invents a special plant protector that works in any scenario - even against a rogue football!
Dangle Disaster. Evil Pea has set a trap for the Tatocar but gets herself and Corn trapped instead.

programmes.show_name: New: Talking Tom Heroes: Suddenly Super
programmes.show_description: The Trouble with Tom. The Rakoonz set up a series of tricks that make Tom doubt his powers.
Postosuchus and Teeth. Children's dinosaur history series. Andy travels back 220 million years to the time of postosuchus - a giant crocodile-like creature.
Pickle Power Girl. Jen and Small are playing superheroes and are ready to save the world.

programmes.show_name: My First Festivals: St David's Day
programmes.show_description: St David's Day. We follow Mollie and her family as they celebrate the wonderful Welsh festival of St David's Day.
Owl Butterfly and Sunbittern. Aneeshwar and Lizzie meet two amazing animals and reveal a surprising connection between them. This time, it's the giant owl butterfly and the sunbittern.
Waffle's Magic. Mrs Hobbs thinks she's magicked Waffle the Wonder Dog away, but Waffle is on an adventure of his own, sniffing for a biscuit backstage.
The Rocking Horse Badge. Animated preschool series. Duggee is tidying when he comes across his old rocking horse, Bucky. The Squirrels help mend Bucky and in return get to ride him.
Porcupine Puffer. Animated deep sea adventures with Captain Barnacles and his explorers. Barnacles, Kwazii and Peso venture inside a whale shark to retrieve a porcupine puffer fish.
Otto's Fancy Friend. Otto's afraid a caterpillar pal will be too fancy to be friends when she's a butterfly.
The Leaning Tower of Pisa, Italy. Animated adventure comedy series. The Go Jetters race to fix the Leaning Tower of Pisa, but has it really been glitched?
The Bedtime Wish  . Rafi's flying bed wish turns bedtime into an adventure. But she realises bedtime is bedtime for a reason when Aunty T magics them safely home.
Chrysalis Creche. TapTap becomes very protective when strange eggs appear in the branches of her tree, so everyone helps to keep the garden nice and quiet.
Pear. Live from the Roots and Fruits theatre, it's the fastest woodwind player - Pear!
Magic Castle. Justin and his friends visit a magical castle, and there's magic with The Great Tumbleeny!
Around the World. Toddlers and their grown-ups explore around the world through play, songs and a story.
Flowery Island. While Kiri is playing with Rockaroonie, Lou sees an island in the middle of the lake that's completely covered in flowers. How can he get there?
Garden Helpers. Fiona calls the Piggies to help tidy up her garden, but they bring along a game that drives them crazy. Can they manage to work and play without causing a big mess?
Mission: Train Station. Guide dog Kika must use her supersight to help Dr Amit catch a train to the city.
Camp Out. Preschool animation. Tee and Mo decide to camp out in the garden, but it seems there is always one more thing from his bedroom that Tee needs to help him fall asleep.
Chasing Clouds. The Game Catchers reach the Jelly Planet and play pillow riding.
Rugby. Elsee joins her friend Karlaine to watch a rugby match and play a game of I-spy.
Park Ranger. Dylan the park ranger wants to protect all the trees and animals in his park, but when an injured bird won't let him get close enough to help, he has to get creative!
Supersecret Swoptops. It's secret agent time when Mojo and Bo think Didi the tractor is up to something fishy. But can the two supersecret spies follow her without being spotted?
Trouble in Peak City. The Heroes get frustrated when Ben's alert system sends them on easy rescues repeatedly.
Compost. Ranger Hamza and the Ramblers learn why composting is good for the environment. They make their own compost pile by layering up lots of green waste and brown waste.
The Piri Rule Book. Flutter is sent to the 'naughty berg' when he falls foul of an ancient Piri rule.
The Salmon Run, Alaska. Glitch sets up an ill-fated 'fishy taxi service' to help the salmon run in Alaska.
There Was an Old Woman Who Swallowed a Fly. Leapy dons a stethoscope out of concern for the old woman who keeps swallowing animals.
Otto's Smelly Feet. When Otto's feet smell like cheese, Vida knows just how to help. Everyone is happy about that except little mouse Sunny-he loves cheese!
The Day We Left. With the ship fixed, it is time to leave Proxima. But should Big Lizard come too?
Circus. Bluey is playing circus with her friends but Hercules wants to play his game instead.
Nikhil and Jay and the Dream Detectives. Nikhil wakes up and misses the end of his amazing dream. Jay helps him find the ending!
It's Time for Poetry. JoJo and Gran Gran read poetry at the library and are inspired to write their own.
Sarah Gets a Cold. Animation. Sarah and her best friend Duck embark on simple but exciting adventures. When Sarah has a cold, Duck helps her enjoy a visit to the doctor.
It Wasn't Me! Animation in which a pair of siblings deal with everyday topics. Lola's imaginary friend persuades her to borrow Charlie's rocket to take an elephant to the jungle.
The Surprising Carrot. Pepi Nana finds a plate of toy carrots on the table in the Toy House, and Mr Onion shares a book about carrots with Dibillo.
Dance. BaBa struggles to follow the steps in MeMo's dance routine, but this doesn't mean BaBa can't dance. With the help of friends, BaBa discovers there are many ways to dance.
Tombliboos' Waving Game. The Tombliboos wave to everyone as they fly through the garden in the Pinky Ponk. The waving game makes everyone in the garden happy.
Sophie Ingle -  When I Grow Up I'd Like to Be. Sophie Ingle reads an inspiring story about dreaming big and choosing your own adventure.
